The paper deals with the problem of devising a closed-loop strategy to control the position of a robot that is tracking a possibly moving target. This problem is a classic one in robotics and control theory, and is typically studied in the context of robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of Kalman Filters, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications. Therefore, these five categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
